Class DLL

java.lang.Object
  DLL
All Implemented Interfaces:
IDLL
public class DLL
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDLL

Class for a doubly linked list. This code implements a standard version of a DLL. In this case the DLL is implemented with a dummy head and a dummy tail node. The instance variables are size (size to the user, thus total size less 2), head, tail, Accessor and mutator methods are: getHead, setHead, getSize, incSize (increment, treated as an accessor), decSize (decrement, treated as an accessor), setSize, getTail, setTail, General methods are: add (wrapper that calls addAtHead), addAtHead (to add a node at the head), contains, containsNode (to run the loop to test containment for contains and remove), linkAfter (optional: link after a given node), remove to remove with a data record as parameter, remove optional: to remove a specific indexed node, toString, unlink to unlink a node.
